name: mars ff0 5
description:
Part of a series of studies exploring the effects of floating point precision arithmetic errors on 3d geometry which are far from origin.

PNG 3840 × 2160

This study of Mars uses public domain data from HiRISE (High Resolution Imaging Science Experiment), the most powerful camera ever sent to another planet, onboard the Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter.

source data (Public Domain): NASA/JPL/University of Arizona
